50|$|While cream ales are top-fermented ales, they {{typically}} undergo {{an extended period}} of <b>cold-conditioning</b> or lagering after primary fermentation is complete. This reduces fruity esters and gives the beer a cleaner flavor. Some examples also have a lager yeast added for the <b>cold-conditioning</b> stage or are mixes of ales and lagers. Adjuncts such as corn and rice are used to lighten the body and flavor, although all-malt examples are available from many craft brewers.|$|E

